    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Study and practice of the therapeutic use of images and objects, to foster nonverbal communication, creativity, and physical interaction, and to uncover verbal associations and interpretations, helping to identify and understand patients' emotional, motor, and perceptual dysfunctions.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estudio y práctica del uso terapeútico de imágenes y objetos, para fomentar la comunicación no verbal, creatividad y la interacción física, y para descubrir asociaciones verbales e interpretaciones, ayudando a identificar y entender disfunciones emocionales, motoras y perceptivas de pacientes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Het bestuderen en uitoefenen van het therapeutische gebruik van beelden en objecten om non-verbale communicatie, creativiteit en lichamelijke interactie aan te moedigen en om verbale associaties en interpretaties bloot te leggen, en als hulpmiddel om de emotionele, motorische en waarnemingsstoornissen van de patient te helpen identificeren en begrijpen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000087757/Woordenlijst Onderwijs Ne-En</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種學術研究與實際操作的治療法，旨在運用圖像與物件，促進非語言的溝通方式、創造力、實際的互動，並且發現言語間的關聯性與詮釋能力，可用於協助查明及瞭解病患在情緒、活動以及感知上出現的障礙。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estudo e prática do uso terapêutico de imagens e objetos, para promover a comunicação não verbal, a criatividade e a interação física, e descobrir associações e interpretações verbais, ajudando a identificar e entender as disfunções emocionais, motoras e perceptivas dos pacientes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
